==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[þreat|þrēat]]'' ‘crowd, army’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/θrɛt/}}
* {{AHD|thrĕt}}, {{SAMPA|/Tret/}}
*{{audio|en-us-threat.ogg|Audio (US)}}

*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛt|-ɛt]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# an [[expression]] of [[intent]] to [[injure]] or [[punish]] another.
# an [[indication]] of [[imminent]] [[danger]].
# a person who is regarded as a danger; a [[menace]].

